# For each service, you need
#   - CFG_NAME that identify the service
#   - CFG_HOST that will be used for this service
#   - CFG_IMAGE_* used to be pull and to create service
#   - CFG_IP ip to use to open service ports (Can be localhost or 0.0.0.0)
#   - CFG_PORT that will define host port used. Can use ramdom number generated by poco (from 1 to 20)
#   - CFG_RESTART restart policy to use with systemd.
#
# Global variables can be used to preset the file
#   - CFG_DOMAIN
#   - DOMAIN_LOCAL
#

# E.g: Basics Configurations
CFG_NAME=name
CFG_HOST=${SERVICE}.${CFG_DOMAIN}
CFG_IP=127.0.0.1
CFG_PORT=${RANDOM_PORT_1}
CFG_IMAGE=docker.io/library/myimage:latest
CFG_RESTART=on-failure
